    "explanation": "<p>$$\\mathrm{BH}_3 \\cdot \\mathrm{THF} / \\mathrm{H}_2 \\mathrm{O}_2 \\cdot \\mathrm{OH}^{-}$$ gives alcohol by anti-Markownikoff's rule.</p>\n<p>$$\\bullet ~\\mathrm{Hg}\\left(\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{COO}\\right)_2 / \\mathrm{NaBH}_4, \\mathrm{OH}^{-}$$ gives alcohol by Markownikoff's rule without rearrangement. There is no carbocation intermediate is formed in this reaction.</p>\n<p>$$\\bullet ~\\mathrm{H}_2 / \\mathrm{Cu} - \\mathrm{Zn}$$ gives alkane and $$\\mathrm{H}_3 \\mathrm{O}^{+}$$ (hydration) gives alcohol by Markownikoff's rule and carbocation intermediate can undergo rearrangement.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lu2dipkz/bb1724c8-ff6f-426d-a805-0f53afd62491/8ba12530-e822-11ee-8788-37c3dae4e435/file-1lu2dipl0.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lu2dipkz/bb1724c8-ff6f-426d-a805-0f53afd62491/8ba12530-e822-11ee-8788-37c3dae4e435/file-1lu2dipl0.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"VITEEE 2022 Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 1 English Explanation\"></p>",
